Subject: Re: [T2] distributor vacuum hose hook up

At 02:59 PM 8/23/2002, Greg Thompson wrote:
>I'm fixing to put dual solex 32-34 PDSIT's back on my '74 single 
>cab....one question:  which carburetor (I believe left) (LIL) and which 
>fitting do I hook the distributor vacuum hose to?  My distributor is an 
>SVDA without retard.  My left carb has 2 vacuum nipples, one right at the 
>throttle plate and one a little further up.  My Bently doesn't show where 
>these hoses hook.  tia, g

Left or right carb, doesn't matter.  Hook it to the port further up on the 
carb (not the one near the throttle body).  The correct port also has a 
smaller OD than the wrong port.

-David

